## `test_mkfs_overwrite_truncates(tmp_db)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fs-4 -->

### Postconditions

```python
mkfs(str(tmp_db))
fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
with fs.as_user(0, 0):
    fs.mkdir("/existing")
fs.close()

# overwrite=True truncates and re-creates.
mkfs(str(tmp_db), overwrite=True)
fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
assert fs.readdir("/") == []
fs.close()
```

